track_notes: From 550, take old Hwy 44 to washed out bridge.  Turn right and follow forest roads to starting point.

From NM 550 proceed about 6.5 miles on a twisty 4wd road to the top of a mesa and the 8012 AZ. The GPS track shown ends at a fence line marking the beginning of Jemez Pueblo land. Set up here or proceed past the fence a few hundred yards to the actual SOTA waypoint.

Alternate route to the mesa top. Though still rugged, this route is easier and considerably quicker than the quote 8012 Up unquote route posted earlier. 

Looked like it might be subject to mud problems when wet.
